<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Taco Stand</title>
    <style type="text/css">
        * { font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; }
        h1 { font-size: 60px; }
        h3 { font-size: 35px; }
        p { font-size: 21px; }
        pre {
            padding: 0;
            white-space: pre-wrap;
            word-break: break-all;
            line-height: 1.5;
            border-left: 5px solid #00c80c;
            background-color: #fafafa;
        }
        code {
            font-size: 21px;
            white-space: pre-wrap;
            padding: 0;
            line-height: 1.5;
        }
        .wrapper { margin: 0 auto; width: 750px; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<% let port = config.server.port !== 80 && config.server.port !== 443 ? ":" + config.server.port : "" %>

<div class="wrapper">
    <h1>Tacostand</h1>
    <p>A simple uploading tool.</p>
    <h3>Uploading a file with curl</h3>
    <hr>
    <p>To upload a file run the following:</p>
    <pre>
        <code>
        curl -F "file=@/my/file/location" <%= host %>
        </code>
    </pre>

    <% let standard_day = config.upload.age.normal > 1 ? "days" : "day" %>

    <p>Which will upload and store a file with a random name for <%= config.upload.age.normal + " " + standard_day %>
        .</p>
    <p>The server will respond with the new location of the file similar to the below example.</p>
    <pre>
        <code>
        <%= host %>spry-pumpkin.jpg
        </code>
    </pre>

    <h3>Uploading a one time access file with curl</h3>
    <hr>
    <p>If you want to upload a file that can only be accessed once do the following:</p>
    <pre>
        <code>
        curl -F "file=@/my/file/location" <%= host %>once
        </code>
    </pre>

    <% let once_day = config.upload.age.once > 1 ? "days" : "day" %>

    <p>Which will work like normal but will only be accessible once and will only be stored
        for <%= config.upload.age.once + " " + once_day %>.</p>

    <h3>Uploading an encrypted file with curl</h3>
    <hr>
    <p>You can store an encrypted file by doing the following:</p>
    <pre>
        <code>
        curl -F "file=@/my/file/location" <%= host %>wrap
        </code>
    </pre>
    <% let wrap_day = config.upload.age.wrap > 1 ? "days" : "day" %>

    <p>Which will upload a file and encrypt it, storing it for <%= config.upload.age.wrap + " " + wrap_day %>.
        The server response will contain the location and password to access it.</p>

    <pre>
        <code>
        <%= host %>spry-pumpkin.jpg
        password: somerandomstring
        </code>
    </pre>

    <p>Check out the source code at <a href="https://github.com/YOUR-WORST-TACO/tacostand">Github</a></p>
</div>
</body>
</html>
